snippet.title: UCL SEMI-FINALISTS! | Real Madrid vs Arsenal (1-2, 1-5 on agg) | UCL Highlights | Saka, Martinelli
snippet.description:
Goals from Bukayo Saka and Gabriel Martinelli capped off a memorable night in the Bernabeu as we booked our place in the semi-finals of the Champions League, and you can see the highlights now.

Saka was denied by Thibaut Courtois from the penalty spot in the first half before Real Madrid were given a spot kick of their own, but referee Francois Letexier ruled out the penalty following a VAR check.

Our number 7 made amends with a superb finish over Courtois in the second half after being played through by Mikel Merino before Vinicius Jr levelled for Los Blancos just two minutes later, but Gabriel Martinelli rounded off a fine evening in the Spanish capital to set up a clash with Paris Saint-Germain.

snippet.title: The global organ trafficking network | DW Documentary
snippet.description:
On the internet, the offer looks very serious: a start to a new life without dialysis, with a new kidney in just a few weeks. A glimmer of hope for seriously ill people who have been waiting for years for a donor organ. Behind it all is a notorious network of international organ traffickers.

We have been following the trail for months. At the center is a transplant clinic in Eldoret, Kenya, where patients from Germany and Israel in particular meet donors from countries in the Caucasus such as Azerbaijan. There are also young Kenyans who are persuaded that they are getting a good deal at 4,000 euros for a kidney. Recipients pay up to €200,000 ($222,000 USD) to organ traffickers. There are many indications that local authorities are looking the other way and that politicians are covering up the trade.
